data.chText: 工作计划；日程安排
data.enText: a plan that lists all the work that you have to do and when you must do each thing

data.chText: 我今后几天的日程紧得要命。
data.enText: I have a hectic schedule for the next few days.

data.chText: 我们的工作安排得很紧。
data.enText: We're working to a tight schedule (= we have a lot of things to do in a short time) .

data.chText: 拍摄如期开始。
data.enText: Filming began on schedule (= at the planned time) .

data.chText: 新桥提前两年落成。
data.enText: The new bridge has been finished two years ahead of schedule .

data.chText: 隧道工程已经晚了工期。
data.enText: The tunnel project has already fallen behind schedule .

data.chText: 列车时刻表
data.enText: a train schedule

data.chText: 从明年开始中文将排进学校的课程表。
data.enText: Chinese will be on the school schedule from next year.

data.chText: （电视或广播）节目表
data.enText: a list of the television and radio programmes that are on a particular channel and the times that they start

data.chText: 这个频道安排的尽是老电影和重播节目。
data.enText: The channel's schedules are filled with old films and repeats.

data.chText: （价格、收费或条款等的）一览表，明细表，清单
data.enText: a written list of things, for example prices, rates or conditions

data.chText: 税率表
data.enText: tax schedules

data.chText: 安排；为…安排时间；预定
data.enText: to arrange for sth to happen at a particular time

data.chText: 会议安排在星期五下午。
data.enText: The meeting is scheduled for Friday afternoon.

data.chText: 安排的活动中有一项是关于替代疗法的讲座。
data.enText: One of the scheduled events is a talk on alternative medicine.

data.chText: 我们在这里停留的时间将超出原先的安排。
data.enText: We'll be stopping here for longer than scheduled.

data.chText: 我预计在5点钟抵达洛杉矶。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: I'm scheduled to arrive in LA at 5 o'clock.

data.chText: 列入，收进（正式目录、清单等中）
data.enText: to include sth in an official list of things

data.chText: 这种物质已被列为毒物。
data.enText: The substance has been scheduled as a poison.

data.chText: 为总统安排日程的官员留出了90分钟的电视采访时间。
data.enText: The President's schedulers allowed 90 minutes for TV interviews.

data.chText: 记事簿用diary或datebook（北美英语），不用agenda。记录约见等事宜也可用台历或挂历（calendar）。diary或journal亦指日记、日志：
data.enText: A book with a space for each day where you write down things that you have to do in the future is called a diary or a datebook ( NAmE ) (not an agenda ). You may also have a calendar on your desk or hanging up in your room, where you write down your appointments. A diary or a journal is also the record that some people keep of what has happened during the day.

data.chText: 安妮•弗兰克的日记
data.enText: the Diary of Anne Frank

data.chText: 在英国英语中，schedule指工作计划、日程安排，timetable指时间表、时刻表：
data.enText: In BrE your schedule is a plan that lists all the work that you have to do and when you must do each thing and a timetable is a list showing the fixed times at which events will happen.

data.chText: 公共汽车 / 火车时刻表
data.enText: a bus/train timetable

data.chText: 在北美英语中，上述两种含义均用schedule。
data.enText: In NAmE these are both called a schedule .

means: (价格、收费或条款等的)一览表，明细表，清单
列入，收进(正式目录、清单等中)

ex.chText: 他安排了一个紧凑的旅行日程。
ex.enText: He has planned a tight travel schedule.

ex.chText: 你已经安排了考试日程吗?
ex.enText: Have you made the examination schedule?

ex.chText: 这项工程提前完工了。
ex.enText: The project was completed ahead of schedule.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事的计划及具体运作的时间表。

ex.chText: 我们必须将这件事提上议事日程。
ex.enText: We must put this item on the agenda.

ex.chText: 会议主席说今天下午有一长串待议事项。
ex.enText: The chairman says there is a lengthy agenda this afternoon.

synonyms.bx: 主要指会议上需要商议解决的问题的一览表。

ex.chText: 他的个人日程表上记着5月5日有个约会。
ex.enText: There is a notation about an appointment on his personal calendar for May 5.

ex.chText: 依照大学的日程表，你们的考试将在7月举行。
ex.enText: According to the university calendar your examinations will be in July.

ex.chText: 总统选举是明年政治日程表上的大事。
ex.enText: The presidential election is the highlight of next year's political calendar.

synonyms.bx: 指某人在记事簿上记下的要做各项事情的计划，也指某个团体或某项活动一年内重大事件的日程安排。

ex.chText: 第一份航空时刻表是在1928年由泛美航空公司刊印的。
ex.enText: The first airplane timetable was published by Pan-American Airways in 1928.

ex.chText: 我这星期的时间安排很紧。
ex.enText: I've got a very busy timetable this week.

ex.chText: 大雾打乱了他们的旅行日程。
ex.enText: The heavy fog upset their timetable for the trip.

synonyms.bx: 比 schedule 更为具体，常指车、船、航班等的时刻表，也指课程表或活动计划的时间表。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：时间表，计划表

ex.chText: 你打算在哪里度假?
ex.enText: Where do you plan to spend your holiday?

ex.chText: 数月来，我们一直在筹划我们的加拿大之行。
ex.enText: We have been planning our trip to Canada for months.

ex.chText: 警方正在调查他何时开始计划逃跑以及他的同谋有谁。
ex.enText: The police are investigating when he began planning his escape and who his accomplices were.

ex.chText: 他不是蓄意隐瞒真相的，只是一时害怕。
ex.enText: He didn't plan to conceal the truth. He was just too scared at that moment.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指事前仔细筹划、安排。

ex.chText: 他们曾密谋抢劫银行。
ex.enText: They had plotted to rob the bank.

ex.chText: 为什么军方密谋推翻他？
ex.enText: Why did the military secretly plot against him?

ex.chText: 他图谋推翻政府。
ex.enText: He plotted to overthrow the government.

synonyms.bx: 通常指秘密策划违法行为或针对某政要、政府的阴谋活动。

ex.chText: 学生们想要更多的时间来准备考试。
ex.enText: The students wanted more time to prepare their exams.

ex.chText: 他们正忙着准备去度蜜月。
ex.enText: They were busy preparing for their honeymoon.

synonyms.bx: 指为将要发生的事情作好计划、安排等。

ex.chText: 会议定于下星期五召开。
ex.enText: The conference is scheduled for next Friday.

ex.chText: 他的第一本书定于10月出版。
ex.enText: His first book is scheduled for publication in October.

synonyms.bx: 指将某事安排在某一时间或日期进行，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 邪恶的皇后密谋毒死小公主。
ex.enText: The evil queen schemed to kill the little princess with poison.

ex.chText: 他总是觉得他的同事们都在算计他。
ex.enText: He always feels that all his colleagues are scheming against him.

synonyms.bx: 指为牟取私利而投机取巧或搞阴谋。

ex.zh: 常规的日程安排（或时刻表）
时间表（或明细表）的变更

tr: a temporally organized plan for matters to be attended to
an ordered list of times at which things are planned to occur
plan for an activity or event
example: I've scheduled a concert next week

tr: plan the time and place for events
example: I scheduled an exam for this afternoon

value.def: A schedule is a plan that gives a list of events or tasks and the times at which each one should happen or be done.

example.ex: He has been forced to adjust his schedule...
example.tran: 他被迫调整了自己的日程安排。

example.ex: We both have such hectic schedules.
example.tran: 我们俩日程安排得都很紧。

value.def: You can use schedule to refer to the time or way something is planned to be done. For example, if something is completed on schedule, it is completed at the time planned.

example.ex: The jet arrived in Johannesburg two minutes ahead of schedule...
example.tran: 喷气式飞机提前两分钟到达了约翰内斯堡。

example.ex: It will be completed several weeks behind schedule.
example.tran: 这将比原计划晚几个星期完成。

value.def: If something is scheduled to happen at a particular time, arrangements are made for it to happen at that time.

example.ex: The space shuttle had been scheduled to blast off at 04:38...
example.tran: 航天飞机已经预定于凌晨 4 点 38 分发射升空。

example.ex: A presidential election was scheduled for last December...
example.tran: 总统选举原计划在去年 12 月举行。

value.def: A schedule is a written list of things, for example a list of prices, details, or conditions.
value.tran: (价格、细节或条件等的)一览表，明细表，清单

value.def: A schedule is a list of all the times when trains, boats, buses, or aircraft are supposed to arrive at or leave a particular place.
value.tran: (火车、客轮、公共汽车或航班的)时刻表,时间表

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 timetable

value.def: In a school or college, a schedule is a diagram that shows the times in the week at which particular subjects are taught.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 timetable
